Class sps_p.Swarm

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • sps_p.Swarm
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible
    public class sps_p.Swarm
extends javax.swing.JPanel
    sps_p.Swarm is a main class that calculate next position for each particle and paint them. There are 2 ways to calculate next position. The one is open boundary and the second is periodic boundary.

      • timeEvolution

        private java.util.List<Pair<java.lang.Double>> timeEvolution​(java.util.List<sps_p.Particle> particles)
        Calculate the time evolution of ri for all particles that is given by ri = Σ(i!=j) (kij|Rij|^(-1) - |Rij|^(-2)) * ^Rij. Rij = rj - ri, ^Rij = Rij / |Rij|, and kij denotes a constant that represents "to what extent person i prefers person j".
        Parameters:
        particles - All N particles.
        Returns:
        The list of the time evolution for each ri.
